<sect1 id="DecodeBase64">
  <!-- DNT-Start --><title>DecodeBase64</title><!-- DNT-End -->

  <!-- DNT-Start --><para><emphasis role="bold">STD.Str.DecodeBase64<indexterm>
      <primary>STD.Str.DecodeBase64</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>Str.DecodeBase64</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>DecodeBase64</primary>
    </indexterm>(</emphasis> <emphasis>value</emphasis> <emphasis
  role="bold">)</emphasis> <emphasis role="bold"></emphasis></para><!-- DNT-End -->

  <informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
    <tgroup cols="2">
      <colspec colwidth="80.50pt" />

      <colspec />

      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry><!-- DNT-Start --><emphasis>value</emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

          <entry>A <!-- DNT-Start -->STRING<!-- DNT-End --> value containing the data to decode.</entry>
        </row>

        <row>
          <entry><!-- DNT-Start -->Return:<emphasis> </emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

          <entry>DecodeBase64 returns a <!-- DNT-Start -->DATA<!-- DNT-End --> value.</entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>

  <para>The <emphasis role="bold">DecodeBase64 </emphasis>function returns a
  <!-- DNT-Start -->DATA<!-- DNT-End --> value containing the decoded binary data.</para>

  <para>Example:</para>

  <!-- DNT-Start --><programlisting format="linespecific">IMPORT STD;
str:='AQIDBAU=';
DecodedData:= STD.Str.DecodeBase64(str);
DecodedData;</programlisting><!-- DNT-End -->

  <para>See Also: <link linkend="EncodeBase64">EncodeBase64</link></para>
</sect1>
